rsonal-finance%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1990s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporatefinanceinstitute.com%2Fresources%2Fcareer%2Fhigh-earners-not-rich-yet-henrys%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2000s%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They've%20been%20making%20a%20comeback%20as%20economic%20conditions%20have%20made%20them%20more%20relevant.%20DINK%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20used%20in%20part%20to%20highlight%20the%20financial%20benefits%20of%20not%20having%20children.%20As%20the%20costs%20of%20raising%20children%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-kids-cost-raising-child-inflation-childcare-tax-exemptions-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eballooned%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20DINK%20lifestyle%20has%20started%20to%20resonate%20with%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20difficult%20to%20pinpoint%20just%20how%20many%20Americans%20fall%20into%20each%20category%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20generally%20not%20officially%20tracked.%20But%20the%20terms'%20recent%20popularity%20suggests%20people%20want%20to%20understand%20how%20they%20fit%20into%20the%20broader%20economy%20beyond%20standard%20measurements.%20Together%2C%20they%20offer%20a%20glimpse%20into%20different%20groups%20working%20to%20get%20by.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20part%20of%20why%20they've%20become%20popular%20again%20is%20because%20these%20acronyms%20succinctly%20describe%20various%20forms%20of%20financial%20limbo%20that%2C%20until%20relatively%20recently%2C%20weren't%20well%20represented%20in%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eric%20Anicich%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20organization%20at%20the%20USC%20Marshall%20School%20of%20Business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20track%20of%20them%20all%20is%20crucial%20to%20understanding%20how%20the%20system%20works%2C%20but%20it%20can%20get%20confusing.%20%3Cem%3EHenry%2C%20a%20geriatric%20millennial%20ALICE%20and%20half%20a%20POLK%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20